      <title>For First Time in Decades, Liberia’s Taps Are No Longer Running Dry</title>
      <pubDate>Mon, 12 Nov 2018 08:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>Kate Thomas</author>
      <link>https://www.newsdeeply.com/womensadvancement/articles/2018/11/12/for-first-time-in-decades-liberias-taps-are-no-longer-running-dry</link>
      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/womensadvancement/articles/2018/11/12/for-first-time-in-decades-liberias-taps-are-no-longer-running-dry</guid>
      <description>In Liberia, the Ebola outbreak drove steps to restore water pipes devastated during 14 years of civil war. As well as improving public health and productivity, access to clean, running water will, locals say, help keep girls in education.</description>
