      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/refugees/community/2016/03/23/higher-risk-of-psychosis-among-refugees</guid>
      <description>A study published in the British Medical Journal has found that refugees in Sweden have a substantially higher risk of schizophrenia and nonaffective psychotic disorders than other migrants. We spoke with the study’s lead author, Anna-Clara Hollander of Sweden’s Karolinska Institute.</description>
